Package: planscanR.screen
Title: Score, Classify, and Select Text Records by Topic Relevance
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Bart", "Hoekstra", email = "mail@barthoekstra.nl", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A general-purpose framework for screening text records by topic
    relevance: multilingual embedding cosine scoring, zero-shot
    classification, a lexical keyword layer, and a learned selection model
    over human keep/drop labels. Built for the planscanR family
    (environmental-assessment records) but usable with any tibble of text and
    a topic vector. Brings in the Python toolchain (via reticulate) that the
    leaf planscanR fetcher deliberately avoids.
License: GPL (>= 3)
